author: Daily Herald report
title: Fall farmers market in Libertyville
text: St. Lawrence Episcopal Church, 125 W. Church St., Libertyville, will host a fall farmers market and craft event from 11 a.m. to 4 p.m. Sunday, Oct. 25. Local farmers will sell fresh produce, apples, pumpkins, gourds, honey and more. Visitors also can select from goat soaps, handcrafted jewelry, whimsical creations and paper goods or pre-order fresh balsam wreaths. The Lake County Folk Club will be among the performers at the all-day open mic stage. Refreshments and home-baked goods, as well as gourmet pizzas, will be among the offerings. Call (847) 362-2110.
